description:
Ingredients: 
-1 lb. lean ground beef
-1/2 cup breadcrumbs
-1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese
-1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley
-1 large egg
-1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
-1/2 teaspoon salt
-1/4 teaspoon ground black pepper
-1/2 cup tomato sauce
-1/4 cup water
-1/2 lb. spaghetti

Instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 375°F.

2. In a large bowl, combine ground beef, breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, egg, garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Mix until ingredients are evenly distributed.

3. Form the mixture into 1-inch meatballs and place on a greased baking sheet.

4. Bake for 15-20 minutes, or until the meatballs are cooked through.

5. In a saucepan, combine tomato sauce and water and bring to a boil.

6. Add the cooked meatballs to the sauce and reduce heat to low. Simmer for 10 minutes.

7. Meanwhile, cook the spaghetti in a pot of boiling water according to package instructions.

8. Drain the spaghetti and serve with the meatballs and sauce. Enjoy!
title: Spaghetti Meatball
